{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4114", "repo": "rails", "body": "Yes, that looks good, but you could actually just create the class instance within the test, which will ensure that it is definitely not used elsewhere:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[1] pry(main)> require 'active_record'\r\n=> true\r\n[2] pry(main)> klass = Class.new(ActiveRecord::Base) do\r\n[2] pry(main)*   def self.name\r\n[2] pry(main)*     \"Topic\"\r\n[2] pry(main)*   end  \r\n[2] pry(main)* end  \r\n=> #<ActiveRecord::Aggregations::ClassMethods:0x10f0810>\r\n[3] pry(main)> klass\r\n=> #<ActiveRecord::Aggregations::ClassMethods:0x10f0810>\r\n[4] pry(main)> klass.table_name\r\n=> \"topics\"\r\n```", "_id": {"$oid": "52382c72bd3543c15100f1f0"}, "issue_id": 4114, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3247462", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4114#issuecomment-3247462", "updated_at": "2011-12-22T10:15:25Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "login": "jonleighton", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers", "type": "User"}, "create